div2.entryFree:

                            مَوْثِقٌ
                         and ↓ مِيثَاقٌ
                        A compact; a contract;
a covenant; an agreement; a league; a treaty;
an engagement; a bond; an obligation; a promise. (S, K, &c.)


                            وَحِىٌّ

                        Hasty; (K;) quick; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;
applied in this sense to death. (S, Mgh, Msb.)


                            وَرِكٌ

                        What is above the thigh; [the haunch;
or hip; and often signifying only the hip-bone;
and the hip as meaning the joint of the thigh?]
(S, K, &c.)


                            وَعِْلٌ

                        A mountain-goat: (K, &c.:) see ثَيَنَلٌ;
also أَلْبٌ; and أَرْوِيَّةٌ and شَهْرٌ.
